</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on violence against women, 
its causes and consequences, Rashida Manjoo 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Mission to Solomon Islands</b>*<b> 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i></p>
<p> In the present report, the Special Rapporteur on violence against women, its causes 
and consequences, examines the situation of violence against women in Solomon Islands. 
including violence perpetrated within the family and the community, violence perpetrated 
between 1998 and 2003 (during &#8220;the tensions&#8221;) and violence relating to the development of 
extractive industries. She also examines the State&#8217;s legislative and institutional responses to 
such violence, and makes recommendations thereon. 
</p>
<p> 
 
</p>
<p>  
 * The summary of the present report is circulated in all official languages. The report itself, 
</p>
<p>contained in the annex to the summary, is circulated in the language of submission only. 
</p>
<p> United Nations A/HRC/23/49/Add.1 
</p>
<p> 
